<html>
	<head>
		<meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html; charset=iso-8859-1">
		<title>BCM_GETTEXT</title>
	</head>
	<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF">
		<p><font color="#000000" size="4"><strong>BCM_GETTEXT</strong></font></p>
		<table border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="3" width="100%">
			<tr>
				<td width="100%" bgcolor="#E6E6E6"><pre>BCM_GETTEXT
	wParam = 0;
	lParam = ( LPARAM )( LPTSTR )lpszBuffer;</pre>
				</td>
			</tr>
		</table>
		<p>Retrieves all text from the control.</p>
		<ul>
			<li>
				Returns one of the following:</li>
			<ul type="disc">
				<li>
					Zero for failure.</li>
				<li>
					A global memory handle when the message has allocated the memory for you.</li>
				<li>
					A pointer to the input buffer.</li>
			</ul>
		</ul>
		<dl>
			<dt><em>lpszBuffer</em></dt>
			<dd>
				This can be a pointer to a buffer large enough to hold the text. Use the <a href="gettextlength.htm">
					BCM_GETTEXTLENGTH</a> message to determine the size necessary to store 
				the text.
				<p>If this is zero the routine will allocate the necessary memory for you and return it 
					to you as a global memory handle. You are responsible for dealocating the 
					handle when you are done with it.</p>
			</dd>
		</dl>
		<dl>
			<dt><strong>Note:</strong><dt>
					<dd>
						When there is no text in the control the message will return NULL.
					</dd>
		</dl>
	</body>
</html>
